##ORAL RECORD: Dalian Xiaoqiang's adventures in Wuhan | Wuhan, Wuhan

MICRO-SIGNAL ZGZS001

Introduction, Voice of China, latest news

I'm Claire Kuo, the reporter.

Before I met Xiaoqiang, a young man from Dalian, I had heard about his strange story: He had planned to go to Hunan for business, but he got off the bus in The Wrong Mans. In order not to sleep on the street, he found in the hospital quarantine area cleaning work, so, on the front line of the fight against the epidemic!

In the interview, in his dorm room, where the cleaning crew was staying in a hotel near the hospital, he shared a room with two roommates, and the floor was covered with clothes and food. Many, he says, are from medical teams and well-meaning volunteers.

On the day of the interview, his parents learned about his experiences in Wuhan. My mother seemed a little skeptical. She called me between interviews, and he asked me out loud which media outlet I was from.

In these days always tense atmosphere, the experience of Xiaoqiang rare people can not help but laugh, but listen to his story, behind the belly, also let people shed tears.

I'm Claire Kuo, the reporter.

Before I met Xiaoqiang, a young man from Dalian, I had heard about his strange story: He had planned to go to Hunan for business, but he got off the bus in The Wrong Mans. 1

Which train? I'll never forget it, G576!

My name is Xiaoqiang, this year 28 years old, Dalian, I do Mobile Game Studio.

It's been, like, a good year, you know, with the family, nothing out of the ordinary, just like New Year's, it's been great.

New Year at home, I knew Wuhan side of the epidemic, the country began to serious. I bought a mask early, and I bought a lot of masks, because it was advertised. I Know Wuhan will be "closed" on January 20th, it is the center point.

After the New Year, I went back to work. My studio, to put it bluntly, is a computer, I am relatively free in this line of work, there is no work to do not go to work. On the contrary, I will earn more when everyone is on vacation, because everyone is playing mobile games in the New Year.

Every year I need to go to Changsha to meet my master to buy the software needed this year. Every year, whoever gets it first might make a little bit more. My master is in Yueyang. I was going to join him in Changsha.

I was supposed to fly to Changsha on February 13th. That day noon decided, but one look, afternoon ticket is too expensive, more than 2000. Well, I guess I'll pass. Let's see if we can find another way.

It was then found that it was cheaper to fly from Shenyang to Shanghai and from Shanghai to Changsha, saving about seven or eight hundred yuan. I thought, take out more than a hundred dollars, in Shanghai to find a hotel for a night, the next morning to leave, is not quite good, right? It'll save you six hundred bucks, eight hundred bucks.

At first, I wanted to go straight to Changsha, but then my master said, why don't you come straight to Yueyang East and I'll drive you there. I mean, that could work, right? SWITCH PLACES! I'm just GONNA go.

I set off from Dalian to Shenyang, from Shenyang to Shanghai Pudong, from Shanghai Pudong to Hongqiao high-speed Railway Station, from Hongqiao high-speed railway station to take the high-speed railway to Changsha, no more than a whole day, to Changsha.

Which train? I'm so impressed, I'll never forget it! G576!

Later, I looked into why the train was passing through Wuhan, because when I first bought the ticket, I didn't see... who cares when they first bought the ticket? Would notice where it was parked? Later, after I was stranded in Wuhan, I repeatedly looked, check the stop, I can now show you, you see... it does not have Wuhan! After Lu'an, go straight to Yueyang East, then Miluo East, then Changsha South, done! It does... it doesn't have Wuhan!

I arrived in Shanghai on the 14th. On the 15th, from Hongqiao to East Yueyang. The train leaves from Hongqiao at 8:30 or 40, and then it should be about 3:00 p.m. in Changsha, and it should be about 2:00 p.m. in Yueyang East.

So I got on the train, and when I got on the train, I was in car 3. Around 12:00 noon, 11:00,12:00, I don't remember, the first night had only one instant noodles, did not eat in the morning, hungry, asked the steward, "where is the dining car? " She told me the number 8 car, good, then go! Buy A box of rice, car 8, sit down, eat it, stay, don't leave.

My period's over. Because I saw after the last station, there is no middle station, should be directly to the east of Yueyang. Well, then I guess it has to be. But I couldn't quite tell the time, so I looked out the window -- Foshan Station!

Because everybody knew at that time Wuhan is what circumstance, I also know! The heart is... How did this arrive Wuhan Station? But I didn't think I was GONNA get out. It's okay. You just got here.

When the carriage door opened, I unconsciously covered my mouth with my mask because of the Gust of wind.

At that time, we Dalian seems to have only a dozen cases, once because of a confirmed case, so we are worried about, let alone Wuhan so many cases, I was sure to cover my mask ah!

I saw everyone getting off the bus, and I was a little shocked. Here, can I get off? !

I see me next to a family of three, husband and wife with a child, they actually wear protective clothing off the car! In front of him was an old man, who had once communicated with the conductor. He didn't understand what he was saying, but I saw him take out some kind of certificate, and some kind of certificate, and showed it to the conductor. I didn't pay much attention in the back because I could only see in the front.

Then the conductor came up and said, why don't you get off? I said, why did I get out of the car? I went east to Yueyang. She said, most of this car is Wuhan people, people are getting off, you should get off. I said I was not from Wuhan, she said you in which car? I said I was in car 3, she said, so why are you in Car 8?

They didn't have such a strong attitude that they had to let me out of the car, but what did they tell me? For the safety of the whole car, it was impossible for me to go back to car 3 again, and it's not gonNa keep me going. Because I was surrounded by people from Wuhan -- I was literally surrounded by people from Wuhan, and then there was no way.

You know, my mom always told me that you had a character flaw, that you should learn how to say no to people. She told me to get out of the car, and I didn't want to get out, but I saw the bad news, and security wouldn't let me in, and there was a fight, right? Eventually, the troublemakers will all be punished, and I don't want to make trouble.

And I thought, if you can stop, if you can get out, then you can get in, right? If someone comes down, it means the high-speed train station is still open. I'll go up to the high-speed train station. I'll go down and buy another ticket to East Yueyang. It's easy.

Then I got out of the car. When I went down there, I knew it might not be what I thought it would be. There was no one in the hall, only the old man I saw, and a girl behind me after I stood up. She was carrying a suitcase. Only two people were standing there. The rest were gone.

2

I'm just passing through. I'll make it

I know I may not be able to go today, but at that time, I did not feel that I would stay in Wuhan, I think I must be able to go. Because of what? I did not stay in Wuhan, I just pass by, isolation I admit, I can go.

Out of the platform, into the lobby of the high-speed train station. I looked at the ticket counter and there was no one there; the whole station was empty! There's no crew, no one. And then I knew I couldn't get a ticket.

But I think, I can walk, I wait until this time tomorrow, can I walk? He opens the door, I get in, right? I'll just buy another ticket for tomorrow, or I'll just get on the bus and I'll be on my way.

Here's what I think. The idea is good, the reality is cruel.

Then I'll search the hotel. The first step is the hotel. No Hotels Open. I use Meituan, hungry, wechat elong city search, no hotel business. Some can place an order, but there is absolutely no answer on the phone.

Next thing I know, I'm calling a cab. Call a cab. If you call a cab and go to a hotel nearby, should be easy? I can't get a cab. There's no cab. And then I called 110, and 110 told me that there were only 120 cars available. You Call 120. I gave 120 dozen, 120 also said, no car, can not pick you up.

Later, I wanted to search for "volunteers. ". I'm not here to volunteer. I'm here to find volunteers. I'm GONNA Google "volunteer" across town, and I'm GonNa Start Typing.

But the same city on the search for "volunteers" , it popped up is "recruitment of volunteers" ! But there are four words that caught my eye: "Eat and live. ". I mean, it's a living room, it's a living room, right?

I didn't think at the time that I would come to work in Wuhan. I just wanted to fool around for a day and look for opportunities to go. If I couldn't, I would fool around for another day and look for opportunities to go. My strong feeling at the time was, "I can go, " because I'm not from Wuhan, AH, i can go anywhere. I'M NOT FROM WUHAN!

The first call was not to the hospital, the first call was for a security guard, and it was quite far from the high-speed railway station. He said that the traffic was tight and very tense at that time. He said there was nothing he could do. "We don't have the right to go through so many checkpoints and can't pick you up. ".

And then I made a second call, and this is the number for the city. And he says, "Do you have a car? " I say I don't have a car, he says you can't do this without a car, we have to run all over the city, all over the place, I need you to go where you're going to sterilize you have to drive.

I said, well, then I'll make another phone call. This call was made to Wuhan First Hospital. He said yes, but I have to call your car. If you wait a few minutes, see if there's a car, I'll let you know. After a few minutes, only to call me, "a car. ". But tell me, you have to wait here for 40 minutes, an hour, it's a long way away.

I said, "okay, wait. I can't find a car anyway. ".

I was like, "you got me. You got to bring me that, right? "? You put me to work, don't you have to train? I don't know anything. You have to train. You trained for a day or two, I spent a day or two looking for opportunities, I left, I just mixed two days.

3

I feel like I'm not wrapped up in anything

When I came to the hospital that night, I had nowhere to stay, so I stayed in the basement, and there was a cot set up next to the security room.

What I was thinking was, I'd find a way to leave the next day, not do it. And then, the next morning, they wake us up for work. I thought it was just a simple training session, breakfast and then training, but I didn't think it was just to let us upstairs.

The supervising teacher helped me to wear the clothes, that is to wear the protective clothing! There were two or three people, some of whom had just finished volunteering at Thor Mountain. Because there was no work on Mount Thor, and I couldn't go back after volunteering, and then I went up here to look for work.

I was scared to death the first time I came into the room.

Really is, after changing clothes, I always feel that there must be some part of my body is not wrapped, that is, I feel this trip in, out is definitely not me, must be 100% infected.

I always feel exposed everywhere, always feel unsafe, always think I will be infected. The first time I took the lunch box, I put my hand under the lunch box and found that it was sticky... at that moment, there were gloves, but I felt the soup would seep in. "Ah, maybe IT'S INFECTED! "

What are we GONNA do? Take the lunchbox and put it in slowly. You do everything on Tiptoe.

When I went to mop the floor, she told me, boy, are you drawing flowers on the floor, I couldn't do it the normal way, so I thought I'd take a breath at the door, hold it, go in, mop it up, get it out, spit it out, and breathe again. That's it. That's it.

In this way, did two or three days, at night can not sleep, night time is always used to search for "how to leave Wuhan. ".

In fact, at the beginning, it is easier to speak with your family. It is easier to open your mouth. The further you go, the harder you open your mouth. You don't know how to say to your family, "I've arrived in Wuhan! " When you say you've arrived, you don't say earlier. It took you more than 20 days to say, didn't you? The more you go back, the harder it is to open your mouth, the harder it is to explain to your family.

Because at first I was confident enough, I felt that I could walk by myself. I think since the high-speed railway stops here, can I get on it? It's pretty simple. You can stop, can't you? Why don't you let the servants in if they can help you, right? Yeah, I think so.

I really didn't think about why the high-speed train passed through Wuhan... I didn't... I didn't pay attention when I bought the ticket, who cares if it passed through where... but later I found out that it didn't pass through Wuhan, this is the car, the G576.

Couldn't sleep, spent the night searching for a way out of the hospital, how to walk. Did Not Search, can search is "2000 yuan to take you out of Wuhan" that kind of small advertising. I believe it! I tried. I couldn't get through. After three or four days, a little feeling finished, as if really can not go, too confident, blind self-confidence.

Scared, just scared, really scared, just really scared, nothing else. Seeing patients every day, you said that in our local area, after a patient appeared, the whole city followed with tension. So Wuhan, so many patients..

I remember the next day or the third day, the day fifteen thousand cases were diagnosed, and on that day, what was my mood? I was supposed to be at work by then, fifteen thousand, fifteen thousand a day, who knows what's GonNa happen the next day, right?

I'm so scared, I feel like it might be over, like I'm never gonNA get home.

Cleaning is to clean up the garbage, mop the floor, disinfection... so, and then repeat, once in the morning, once in the afternoon, at night is to take out the garbage. Tip Toe, let's be honest, you see you need to look up, my clothes, the first time wearing close to the body like I keep what I do, try not to move it, that is the state, a state of stiffness. Four and a half hours in the morning, three and a half hours in the afternoon, and four hours in the evening, 12 hours in total. Every day like this, you can't drink water, you can't go to the toilet, so just hold on.

I once thought too tired, changes a work, even if can not walk, then changes a work, okay?

Yeah, they're hiring at hospitals, and they're not opening anywhere else, and they're not opening doors, and he's not hiring. They're hiring in hospitals, so it doesn't matter where you go.

4

They are not the gentle women of Nanjing, they are more "men" than I am

My friend in Yueyang tried to get a pass to come in and pick me up, and then for two days, he said, man, I'm too limited, I can't do it, if you need something, I'll find a way to get it to you, I can't get in. When I knew I might not be able to leave, I did panic, and then I tried to save myself.

Because I don't know any media, but I know you media are powerful, right? It is powerful. I contacted our Dalian traffic broadcast public number, in the public number message, did not expect, Dalian traffic broadcast the next day to see!

Called me all morning, and my phone was in my suit, and I couldn't get it out. At lunch time, take out a look, Dalian number. They called me. They didn't find me. They texted me. As soon as I saw the message, it was really Dalian traffic broadcast. I felt that it was a lifesaver. Dalian traffic broadcast, in my heart status, feel they can do anything Ah, find them, find hope! I said, can you help me contact the Dalian medical team?

Actually, I overestimated their abilities, which I didn't know until later, and they didn't have access to the medical team. And everything they did for me afterwards was, indeed, out of their depth.

They tried to find someone to help me contact the Dalian medical team, contact their Dalian medical team doctors. Then I got in touch with some local volunteers in Wuhan to help me, send something or other.

The next day or the next day, they would have hooked me up. And then the medical team said, if you need something, if you want something, you let us know, and if there's anything going on there, or if you're not feeling well, you let us know.

When I did, I was so happy. But I didn't let my guard down on the ward. I did not say that I suddenly feel not afraid, no, I am still a little afraid, but not as strong as before. Little by little, is accustomed to, did not say which moment, I contacted Dr. Liu, I think Dalian people know me, I am not afraid, no. I'm scared now, but... it's not as strong as it used to be.

I've never been to Wuhan before, and I don't have any friends in Wuhan... Xishuangbanna, isn't it further South Than Wuhan? Then Wuhan is not the southernmost place. Wuhan is far south for me. Anyway, I used to watch TV and say how Wuhan was, although I knew in my heart that the Chinese epidemic was very serious, but it didn't seem to have anything to do with me, you know? It's far away from me. I can't get to Wuhan. At that time, I felt as soon as I heard that people from Wuhan came out, everyone should stay away from him. "How many people can be infected by a Wuhan Person? " I never thought I would come to Wuhan.

Roommate? Very good, he used to work in Dalian for a long time, I speak Dalian he can understand, but he spoke I do not understand, he is from Jiangsu. He can understand me, that's all. He went to Hebei to look for a job, and when the Hebei side was not working, he came here to Wuhan. I heard a friend of his called him.

Every day, in fact, nothing, just like ordinary work, every day to work, work, eat, work, work, eat. But it's exhausting! I have a basin of clothes soaking in the bathroom, want to wash! When I left in the morning, I thought I would wash it at noon today. When I finished my work, I went back to the hotel and looked, forget it, I'll wash it at night.

Now I wear protective clothing, has been very skilled, practice makes perfect! Oh, it's really dressed very quickly, and very well! Once after wearing I said: "teacher, you help me look, I wear any gap, there is no flaw? " She said, you do not have to see, you are better than I wear!

I wear three a day, one in the morning, one in the afternoon and one in the evening. Well, it's complicated when you take it off.

After arriving here, because I did not have any clothes, the First Hospital of Wuhan provided me with some clothes. Look, the quick-drying clothes inside were provided to me by the First Hospital of Wuhan. Then we Dalian medical team sent me shoes, socks, underwear... because I did not intend to stay out long, wearing a suit of clothes, a boy does not change for a day or two, in my opinion is normal, who will take so many clothes?

These, from the Harbin Medical University medical team. There are so many people who help me.

I especially want to thank... Dalian traffic broadcast, that is the first help me, I will never forget! Then Drum Tower Hospital, my floor. My floor is filled with doctors and nurses from the Drum Tower Hospital in Nanjing. I admire them. They are not gentle women from Nanjing. They are all "men" . They are "men" !

The first day I went in, I saw them giving shots, and I had to hold their hands, and it just... It just happened! You touch it with gloves on! That, in my opinion, is a move that is 100 percent infectious! I really admire them. They're amazing.

But now, looking at them, I dare touch them. Now nothing, psychological pressure may be no, there is no burden. At that time, when I was afraid of infection, I asked all kinds of questions, asking about this and that, how could I be infected, how could I prevent infection? I didn't believe what one person said to me. I had to prove it in the mouth of the second person; the second person said to me, i have to prove it to the third person, prove everything they say is true.

Not Now. Now I teach them. I tell them it's not contagious. Now there are some new medical teams... they certainly don't need me to tell them how to prevent it, they know it better than I do, but they take off their Hazmat suits, because I go to work at night, so I help them.

I do learn fast, but I feel like I forget fast. (what's so funny about that?) Of course, I don't think I'll ever wear a hazmat suit again.

5

Compared to them, I'm too ordinary

I feel like the more interviews I do now, the harder it is for me to keep going, and I don't want that anymore.

Our Municipal Party Committee Secretary informed me at midnight that the director of the Municipal Party Committee's Publicity Department contacted me and said that you were relieved that we people in Dalian were all behind you, which made me feel that I, a common people, usually contact a director or something, , , , right?

I can't believe it. Up until now, I've felt like it wasn't real, like it was a dream.

Let's talk about how it got to this point -- Harvard -- I'm not saying how hot I am or anything, but it's way above the average person's pay grade, right?

I'm just a regular guy. To put it bluntly, doctors and nurses do more than we do, right? The real volunteers, they come with the mood, with the ambition, with the will to fight the epidemic, right? And more recently, our cleaning crew, our older aunts, our older uncles, I'm a young guy, and I probably don't do any more than any of them, right? I'm more of a person than they are.

At that time, I contacted the Dalian communication radio station for only one purpose, that is to contact the medical team in Dalian. I was afraid that something would happen in the future. That fellow townsman would certainly take care of me, right? Dalian communications radio said, you can rest assured, we will continue to pay attention to you, and did not say help me find the media, AH, this did not.

It was just a chat. A Guy I know at the nurses'station, his relative's a journalist. He told me, "I'm just going to talk to you, " and after that, "I'm going to make an article about what I'm talking to you and post it to my friends. ". Friend Circle, in my opinion, I send a friend circle, 5 LIKES CAN NOT EXCEED! The friend zone thing, right?

However, I underestimated their friend circle, I underestimated the power of the circle of friends retweet. On the first night, the reading was 10,00020,000, and I thought I was happy with 10,00020,000. At twenty thousand, I thought maybe it was all the people from the hospital. I was well known at the hospital, and I was happy. In the morning, when I was forty thousand, I was happy. By noon the next day, I began to have a phone call, I feel, as if I can not become a "Internet celebrity" that right? I didn't think it would come to this.

I think I'm okay, and now I just want the heat to go away, and everyone forgets about me. Everyone with the brush that short video is same, you see this point like much, everybody thinks quite interesting, point like, brush past! That's what I'm hoping. You Swipe it, it's gone. It's over. Know a Dalian young man has worked here, well, focus on not in me, brush past, brush past as soon as possible! The best thing to do is start tomorrow morning, and we'll forget all about it. I'm just a guy.

6

Aren't the Wu Da Cherry Blossoms beautiful? We're here. We're only going once

I lost 13 pounds. When I got here, I was 182 pounds. I'm 169 pounds. I lost 13 pounds. Although thin is a good thing, but so thin son continue to go on, my body is certainly not.

The most ridiculous, "Fei Cheng Wu Rao" called me, said to introduce me to someone, even said that when the epidemic was over, "we will have a program like this, can you come" , to understand the basic situation, ah..

I am especially grateful to our Dalian Party secretary. He said that, through our propaganda department, he told me that he would do everything possible to ensure that my life in Wuhan would be secure, and that he would take the first time to reflect to them what was missing, i would be the first to be contacted if the country has rules or policies that allow people in Wuhan to return home. That's the only thing that makes me feel better.

Moreover, the number of patients in my ward is decreasing every day, and people are leaving the hospital every day. Before, I cleaned 20 wards, half is two people a room, half is three people a room, 50 or 60 people, now only more than 20 people, less than half, and today there are discharged. I'm just looking at the number of discharges, and if everybody's out, do I get to stop working? Then do not have to work, is not it possible to quarantine; all the quarantine, then ready to go home.

There's got to be a day. Aren't Wuhan University Cherry Blossoms Pretty? Come on, let's go.

We want to record the history of Wuhan in the Spring of 2020 through the narration of 10 people.
